OL,5, Media regulator Ofcom has urged all    
OL,6, broadband firms to support low-income  
OL,7, homes by offering discounted packages  
OL,8, known as "social tariffs".             
OL,10,FOfcom has found that only 55,000 out of
OL,11,F4.2 million homes in receipt of        
OL,12,FUniversal Credit are using discounted  
OL,13,Frates.                                 
OL,15,FIt means households on benefits are    
OL,16,Fmissing out on an average yearly       
OL,17,Fbroadband saving of #144 each.         
OL,19,FMany families are facing added pressure
OL,20,Ffrom the cost of living crisis.        
